                                  Minimum Requirements for Carrier Vessels

66.-(1) Every carrier vessel shall be equipped with refrigerated or
               insulated containers for storage of prescribed products which shall-
                      (a) be insulated;
                      (b) be smooth, light-coloured and impact and abrasion resistant;
                      ( c ) have covered internal corners;
                      (4 be of non-corrodible and non-toxic material;
                      (el be covered and self draining;
                      V) be capable of holding an adequate supply of ice or have alternative
                           means cf cooling or chilling, as the circumstances may require;
                      (g) not   be capable of transmitting any harmful properties or
                           characteristicsto prescribed products;
                      (h) be positioned to prevent contamination of the products by-
                                   (I) fuel used for propulsion of the vessel;
                                  (ii) oil;
